name: Aident AI | Create tool agents with a single click

children.name: A set of endpoints for GPT to interact with user's active browser tab through Aident Companion Extension. GPT can read content from the tab and control/interact with this tab through sending Puppeteer commands to the extension, which are run in the sandbox environment within user's browser.

POST /api /extension /interactable /node /fetch Obtain the Interactable Node objects for the current tab to interact with the page elements. Derived from Puppeteer's Accessibility API, it details the page's structure and content. If the content is too large, use configs to collapse.

POST /api /extension /interactable /node /handle Get the Puppeteer Element Handle using the interactable node id. Control the element through Puppeteer's ElementHandle APIs. Allowed actions include but not limited to `$`, `$$`, `click`, `hover`, `select`, `uploadFile`, `type`, `scrollIntoView`, etc.

Get the Puppeteer Element Handle using the interactable node id. Control the element through Puppeteer's ElementHandle APIs. Allowed actions include but not limited to `$`, `$$`, `click`, `hover`, `select`, `uploadFile`, `type`, `scrollIntoView`, etc.
POST /api /extension /interactable /page /handle Get the Puppeteer PageHandle to control the browser's current tab, using Puppeteer's PageHandle APIs.
Get the Puppeteer PageHandle to control the browser's current tab, using Puppeteer's PageHandle APIs.

POST /api /extension /interpreter /execute Send a command to Typescript/JavaScript interpreter to execute one line. Async functions are executed sequentially, and the result of the last line is returned.
Send a command to Typescript/JavaScript interpreter to execute one line. Async functions are executed sequentially, and the result of the last line is returned.
GET /api /extension /ping Send a ping to the extension and receive a `pong` as response if everything goes well.
